<p class="benefit" style="font-size:18pt;">
	Ever wondered what happens to your invitations when they go in the post box?
</p>
			
			<p class="benefit">
	Does a magic fairy with clean hands magically fly them to their destination?</p>


			<p class="benefit">No.</p>
 

			<p class="benefit">They are handled by at least a dozen different people, pressed between rollers, rained-upon and X-rayed&mdash;just for starters. </p>


			<p class="benefit">All of this means that there without careful consideration, your invitation may well not arrive in the same state you posted it in. </p>


			<p class="benefit">One bride was devastated to find that when her guests received her invitation, the ink had transferred to the other side of the card, causing a horrible, smudged, ghosting effect. </p>


			<p class="benefit">Another common issue is Fat Envelope Syndrome&hellip;</p>

	<img src="/images/homepage/big_illustrations/box_envelope.png" style="margin:0 auto;width:650px;display:block;" />

			<p class="benefit">&hellip;standard envelopes aren't designed to take invitations with a ribbon or an embellishment such as a diamante. They are meant for flat cards only.</p>


			<p class="benefit">Added extras will give the envelope a horrible, unsightly bulge, you won't be able to seal them neatly, and to top it off when they are in the post, the knot on the ribbon or the envelope will often get pushed against the envelope so hard that it will actually cause the envelope to rip and can end up poking through.</p>


			<p class="benefit">Diamantes can press against other enclosures as well as the envelope causing unsightly scars and indents. </p>


			<p class="benefit">Rain will often cause handwritten addresses to run if you use soluble ink, and the same can go for ink printed with inkjets. </p>


			<p class="benefit">This isn't how you want your invitation to arrive. </p>


			<p class="benefit">We know all the nasty things that can happen to an invitation in transit and so we design our invitations to make that journey as safe as it can be.</p>


			<p class="benefit">Our box-envelopes, made from sturdy matching card, are created especially to hold invitations with added extras and keep them in pristine condition.</p>


